{
  "texts": [
    "Each cue is corrupted by flipping randomly chosen neurons between active and inactive and is set as the initial network activity.",
    "During retrieval, the network is asynchronously updated via Glauber dynamics 36.",
    "That is, at each simulation timestep, one neuron is randomly selected to be updated (Fig. 3C).",
    "If its total input from other neurons exceeds a threshold θ, then it is more likely to become active; conversely, subthreshold total input makes silence more likely.",
    "The width of the sigmoid function in Fig. 3C determines the softness of the threshold."
  ]
}